The paper presents algorithms for solving flow and regression problems on graphs, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of adaptive preconditioning and tree-routing based ultra-sparsification suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.NA (numerical analysis) categories. The paper also discusses the connection between flow problems and max-flow/min-cut, which is a topic in cs.CG (computational geometry). The use of semi-supervised learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of convex objectives, which may suggest that it belongs to the cs.IT (information theory) category.
